content.description: Start right of the small undercut on an obvious larger hold. Angle up and left to the hueco shared with Arborist right using underclings and crimps on the slab. Requires a good cleaning most of the time.
content.location: This problem is located along with both Arborist problems on a small undercut left of a long section of mossy low angle slab, well past all the roped climbing. This problem begins on the right side of the undercut.

content.description: Start on an obvious jug on the far right of the Osage Chiefs undercut. Head left under a hanging orange blocks using small small crimps and cool footwork. Stick a big move to the finishing jug on Osage Chiefs Center and top out.
content.location: The Osage Chiefs are located in a small undercut on the right side of the trail. Look for a grey shield of perfect rock leading to a ledge at around 8 or 10 feet. Orange rock underneath the shield yields a number of small crimp rails. These rails should generally be chalked up, making the area relatively easy to identify. OC right takes the rightmost obvious start.

content.description: The easiest line out of the cave. Start low and follow obvious chalked jugs to an exciting topout.
content.location: The Osage Chiefs are located in a small undercut on the right side of the trail. Look for a grey shield of perfect rock leading to a ledge at around 8 or 10 feet. Orange rock underneath the shield yields a number of small crimp rails. These rails should generally be chalked up, making the area relatively easy to identify. OC Left is the leftmost line.

content.description: Start as for Osage Chiefs Left on an obvious jug, instead heading right out the sick thin crimp rail, eventually making a big move to a flat, orange jug. Top out the shield as usual. Engaging movement makes up for a relative lack of height.
content.location: The Osage Chiefs are located in a small undercut on the right side of the trail. Look for a grey shield of perfect rock leading to a ledge at around 8 or 10 feet. content.description:
Old problem put up several years ago now, just remembering it. 

 Sit start on right exit of the cave, work up pitch line.
Follow a left angling slopey rail to a big sidepull jug and top out the easy slab. Quite a good lowball problem.
content.location: Located on the left side of an undercut left of a section of mossy slab. Look for the obvious hueco in the slab above the undercut. Starts on the left angling rail and follows the feature to its end.

content.description: Start on the left side of the undercut on a left angling flake(Arborist Left), heading straight up though amazing slopey grips and eventually grabbing the obvious hueco above the undercut. Any beta I've seen involves a bad LH pinch and a big RH move to the bottom of the hueco. Quite hard for the grade.
content.location: Located on the left side of an undercut left of a section of mossy slab. Look for the obvious hueco in the slab above the undercut. Starts on the left angling rail and heads straight up.

content.description: Boulders scattered to the west of the established sport climbs. Tons of boulders in this zone, and plenty that are cleaned/chalked but as of yet, remain undocumented.
